---
description: Python coding standards
globs:
  - "**/*.py"
  - "**/pyproject.toml"
alwaysApply: true
---

- All IO-bound operations MUST be `async def`
- Type hints are mandatory (Python 3.12+ syntax: use `X | Y` not `Optional[X]`)
- Use Pydantic V2 `model_validate` patterns for data models
- Use `uv run` to execute scripts, NOT bare `python`
- All functions and classes require docstrings (PEP 257)
- Tests go in `./tests`, use pytest only (no unittest)
- NEVER use placeholder comments like `# TODO: implement this` or `# ...rest of code`
- Before importing a package, verify it exists: run `uv pip show <package>` first
